  "doc_id": "37969",
  "text": "Metabolic imaging-FDG PET/CT classically shows asymmetric basal ganglia and cortical hypometabolism contralateral to the patient's affected side (Figs. 1B-1D ). Frequently this is manifested by left-sided cerebral hypometabolism in the context of rightsided symptoms [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The parietal and, to a lesser extent, frontal lobes are frequently involved early in the disease process. Interestingly, studies have revealed hypermetabolism in the basal ganglia and cortex ipsilateral to the clinically affected side [CITATION_3] .",
